&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us 👋&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Life Trading is a growing proprietary trading company with offices in London and Sydney. We combine disciplined execution, quantitative research, and technology-driven trading across global futures markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our culture is relaxed but high-performing, with a flat structure that values accountability, collaboration, and work-life balance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role 💡&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Junior Futures Trader&lt;/strong&gt; to join our London office. This is a hands-on role combining live futures trading, quantitative research, and strategy optimisation within a fast-moving and collaborative environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work closely with traders, developers, and quantitative researchers to improve trading systems, analyse market behaviour, and contribute to new trading ideas and execution improvements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Mission at Life Trading 🎯&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trading&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage risk as part of a 24-hour global trading team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and adjust parameters across proprietary trading systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support live trading operations and desk coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to trading performance and execution quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research &amp;amp; Strategy Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research macroeconomic themes and market-moving events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in market briefings and idea generation discussions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform data analysis using Python and Microsoft Office tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct market microstructure analysis using proprietary backtesting frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in improving trading systems and strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse strategy performance metrics and support software UAT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with developers and quantitative researchers on new tools and features&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow company values, policies, and operational standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to exchange rules, risk frameworks, and compliance obligations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support operational and administrative tasks as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For 👀&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–3 years’ experience trading futures markets or working within a trading environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interest in global macro and futures markets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong numerical and analytical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced proficiency with Microsoft Office tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Python capability or strong interest in developing these skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to multitask in fast-moving market environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear communication skills and strong attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points For ✅&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience within a proprietary trading or quantitative trading environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to systematic or algorithmic trading strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with market microstructure analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic C++ knowledge or willingness to learn&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in improving trading tools, systems, or processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
